## Development History:

- Original Concept: 2023-2024

  - Educational music practice software
  - Based on Ebbinghaus memory curve
  - Desktop application (C# WPF)

- C# Desktop Version: 2024-2025

  - Windows desktop application
  - Full feature implementation
  - Reference code in /01ReferentieBronCode/

- Electron Port: 2024-2025

  - Cross-platform web/desktop app
  - JavaScript/HTML5 implementation
  - Modern web technologies

- Open Source Release: December 2025
  - Dual licensing model (AGPL-3.0 + Commercial)
  - Public GitHub repository
  - Community contributions welcome

## Source Code Attribution:

All source code files are developed by Frank De Baere unless explicitly
marked otherwise within the file headers.

Key Components:

- Ebbinghaus Engine (EbbinghausEngine.js, EbbinghausEngine.cs)
- Adaptive Tau Manager (AdaptiveTauManager.js, AdaptiveTauManager.cs)
- Personalized Memory Calibration (PersonalizedMemoryCalibration.js/.cs)
- Memory Stability Manager (MemoryStabilityManager.js/.cs)
- Intensity Module (IntensityModule.js/.cs)
- Interleaved Session Manager (InterleavedSessionManager.js)

All original algorithms, implementations, and designs are by Frank De Baere.

